Option.name: CHOWN_CTIME_UPDATE_MARK
Option.Value: we mark st_ctime for update always
we mark st_ctime for update only if owner!=-1 or group!=-1

Option.name: FS_NAME_BASENAME_SLASH_STATE
Option.Value: we allow only one slash returned by call of basename("\\");
we allow only two slashes returned by call of basename("\\");
we allow both one and two slashes returned by call of basename("\\");

Option.name: FS_NAME_DIRNAME_SLASH_STATE
Option.Value: we allow only one slash returned by call of dirname("\\");
we allow only two slashes returned by call of dirname("\\");
we allow both one and two slashes returned by call of dirname("\\");

Option.name: POSIX_IO_TERM_OPEN_WITHOUT_NOCTTY_BEHAVIOUR
Option.Value: the terminal always becomes the controlling terminal
the terminal never becomes the controlling terminal
the terminal may becomes the controlling terminal

Option.name: POSIX_PROCESS_FENV_OVERFLOW_RAISING_BEHAVIOUR
Option.Value: feraiseexcept() shall raise the inexact exception whenever it raises the overflow
feraiseexcept() shall not raise the inexact exception whenever it raises the overflow
feraiseexcept() may raise the inexact exception whenever it raises the overflow

Option.name: POSIX_PROCESS_FENV_UNDERFLOW_RAISING_BEHAVIOUR
Option.Value: feraiseexcept() shall raise the inexact exception whenever it raises the underflow
feraiseexcept() shall not raise the inexact exception whenever it raises the underflow
feraiseexcept() may raise the inexact exception whenever it raises the underflow

Option.name: IS_WCONTINUED_DEFINED
Option.Value: WCONTINUED defined
WCONTINUED not defined

Option.name: SETENV_NULL_ENVVAL_BEHAVIOUR
Option.Value: envval can not be equal to NULL
envval can be equal to NULL, but this means error
envval can be equal to NULL, and this means empty envval
